Karena saya mau join ke grup https://t.me/SQLSrvID sudah tidak ketemu linknya. 

Saya mau **tanya** **ttg performance untuk mengirim tabel antar store procedure pada MS SQL Server**. Saya ingin tahu perbandingan dari dua cara di bawah ini :

1. User-defined Table Type 
Saya kurang prefer karena saat susunan data berubah, harus drop and create ulang

2. Table Type. Saya prefer pke ini karena saat  ada perubahaan data cukup ubah column pada SP saja. Contoh implemtasi yg nomor 2 spt berikut:

CREATE PROCEDURE GetItemCount
  @add INT
AS
  DECLARE  @count TABLE (angka INT) 
  INSERT @count
  SELECT SUM(Item) FROM (SELECT 1+@add AS Item) c 
  SELECT * FROM @count ;


CREATE PROCEDURE GetItemCountExecutor
    @add INT
AS
  DECLARE @count1 TABLE (angka INT)
  INSERT @count1
  EXEC GetItemCount @add
  SELECT count(1) FROM @count1 ;

EXEC GetItemCountExecutor 3;
Saya butuh koreksi dari senior sekalian bahwa saya tidak salah jalan.\nğŸ˜ŠğŸ˜ŠğŸ˜Š
Ga lihat benefitnya, kenapa ga langsung select ajağŸ¤”

Kebutuhannya adalah:
- GetItemCount => intinya akan select ke data warehouse kita. Nanti dia akan di consume oleh beberapa SP.
- GetItemCountExecutor => Contoh SP yg akan consume data  dr GetItemCount dg parameter dan diolah.
- Biar di file programming nya tinggal jalanin perintah execute aja. 

Outputnya cuma kalimat untuk keebutuhan reporting

Bentar, gw cariin examplenya.
Istilahnya GoF banget. Lama gak denger ada yang ngomong ini.
Prinsipnya, ada bagian yg harus dipecah jadi dependency class. Jadi, classnya lebih one purpose, klo ada penambahan fungsi, yg ditambahin dependencynya, bukan class utamanya.
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49002/prefer-composition-over-inheritance
Jawaban no. 2 itu cara membedakan kapan milih inheritence ato composition
https://codingdelight.com/2014/01/16/favor-composition-over-inheritance-part-1/
Contoh yg lumayan ngena, part 1 inheritence way, part 2 composition way
Problem paling sering klo penggunaan inheritence berlebihan, biasanya jadi monster class. Classnya juga malah sering diubah klo ada penambahan fitur (ga OCP).
Ambil prinsipnya aja:\nUse inheritence when 2 objects __are__ the same. Use composition when 2 objects __have__ the same behavior/property.

In real world: composition bisa dipake buat bikin sistem yg lebih modular. Misalkan gw bikin library buat convert text markdown ke html. Trus gw share ke publik. Ada request supaya output html support syntax templating (ex: handlebar). Disini prinsip composition dipake. Jadi gw bikin interface semacam IPostProcessor yg akan gw panggil setelah konversi html tapi sebelum direturn. Jadi gw ga perlu develop buat support handlebar, biar community yg develop. Jadi library gw bisa ditambahin fungsinya tanpa mengubah classnya (open for extension, but closed for modification). Begitu seterusnya klo ada fitur tambahan yg dibutuhkan.

berikut qualification nya Software Developer - Frontend

Responsibilities

-  Implementing the front end web application based on the UI/UX design and ticket from Jira.
-  Collaborate with product owners, UX designers, and other stakeholders;
-  Optimizing the web application for performance and scalability
-  Ensuring the web application is compatible across different browser platform
-  Participating in requirements, design and code review 
-  Identify, evaluate and communicate frontend best practices
-  Review, maintain and refactor existing code to meet the requirements for improved or new features
-  Help define coding standards and development processes Willing to learn & adapt different technologies

Requirements

-  Bachelor degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering or Science
-  Knowledge of front-end web technologies: HTML5, CSS, JavaScript , and proficiency in frameworks such Vue and NUXT ;
-  Experience working with Restful API
-  Good troubleshooting and problem solving skills
-  Basic understanding of CSS pre-processing platforms, such as LESS and SASS
-  Proficient with code versioning tools like Git.
-  Experience with common front-end development tools such as Babel, Webpack, NPM, etc.
-  Understanding of the SDLC and Agile development methodology
-  2+ years of experience as a Frontend Developer.


Software Developer - Backend

Responsibilities

-  Develop high performance web api
-  Collaborate with product owners, frontend developer, and other stakeholders;
-  Optimizing the backend application for performance and scalability
-  Participating in requirements, design and code review 
-  Identify, evaluate and communicate backend best practices
-  Review, maintain and refactor existing code to meet the requirements for improved or new features
-  Help define coding standards and development processes Willing to learn & adapt different technologies

Requirements

-  Backend development experience with C# .NET / .NET Core.
-  Good understanding of algorithm complexity, data structures, concurrency & systems performance.
-  Understanding of the SDLC and Agile development methodology
-  Experience with SQL/NOSQL and RDBMS
-  Proficient with Git.
-  Strong object-oriented programming knowledge, familiarity with ORM/Micro ORM (Dapper/Petapoco) technology.
-  Be able to write clear, concise source-code documentation, unit and integration tests.
-  Good troubleshooting and problem solving skills
-  Good knowledge about application integration using RESTFull API and JSON
-  2+ years of experience as a Backend / .NET Developer

@gjulivan  Biasanya pake ini om. Pake https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/microsoft.aspnetcore.mvc.controllerbase.redirecttoaction trus dicombine sama pattern PRG.
Sebelumnya saya sudah sarankan pakai ini tapi requirementnya beda, Om...

Klo ane nangkepnya gini:
1. Form dari web diPOST ke action controller
2. Handler post method bakal validasi inputan form. Hasilnya (invalid atau sukses), bakal diredirect ke action lain (letâ€™s say GetAction)
3. GetAction bakal nampilin hasilnya balik ke form. GetAction harus dapat validation result tanpa merekonstruct inputan ke post action. 

Tujuannya pake redirect: biar nanti klo client refresh browser, ga bakal ngeposy ulang formnya ke web server, tapi diarahkan ke GetAction.

Ini tinggal pakai RSA saja (gak perlu AES, CMIIW). Public key disimpan di aplikasi yg akan didistribusi. Private key disimpan di aplikasi key generator.

Nanti aplikasi client tinggal generate sesuatu yg deterministic saja, encrypt ubah ke base64 kirim ini ke kamu (bisa dengan berbagai cara email, sms, whatsapp).

Di sisi kamu tinggal decrypt dan generate response saja... Kirim response ke customer kmu.

Aplikasi tinggal validasi response apakah sesuai atau tidak... Done...

The CSV file format is __not fully standardized__. The basic idea of separating fields with a comma is clear, but that idea gets complicated when the field data __may also contain commas __or even embedded line breaks. CSV implementations may not handle such field data, or they __may use quotation marks to surround the field.__ Quotation does not solve everything: some fields may need embedded quotation marks, so a CSV implementation may include escape characters or escape sequences.
